{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a015", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 15, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| PRDUR | Duration of Procedure | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Collected duration of a procedure represented in ISO 8601 character format. Used only if collected on the CRF and not derived from start and end date/times. | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": "pr.xpt", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a016", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 16, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| PRTPT | Planned Time Point Name | Char | | Timing | Text description of time when a procedure should be performed. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See PRTPTNUM and PRTPTREF. | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": "pr.xpt", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a017", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 17, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| PRTPTNUM | Planned Time Point Number | Num | | Timing | Numerical version of planned time point used in sorting. | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": "pr.xpt", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a018", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 18, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| PRELTM | Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Planned elapsed time in ISO 8601 format relative to a planned fixed reference (PRTPTREF). This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date/time variable, but an interval, represented as ISO duration. | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": "pr.xpt", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a019", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 19, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| PRTPTREF | Time Point Reference | Char | | Timing | Description of the fixed reference point referred to by PRELTM, PRTPTNUM, and PRTPT. | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": "pr.xpt", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a020", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 20, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| PRRFTDTC | Date/Time of Reference Time Point | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by PRTRTREF in ISO 8601 character format. | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": "pr.xpt", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a021", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 21, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| PRSTRTPT | Start Relative to Reference Time Point | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Identifies the start of the observation as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable PRSTTPT. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": ["STENRF", "Section 4.4.7"], "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": "pr.xpt", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a022", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 22, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| PRSTTPT | Start Reference Time Point | Char | | Timing | Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference point referred to by PRSTRTPT. Examples: \"2003-12-15\", \"VISIT 1\". | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": "pr.xpt", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a023", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 23, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| PRENRTPT | End Relative to Reference Time Point | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Identifies the end of the observation as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable PRENTPT. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": ["STENRF", "Section 4.4.7"], "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": "pr.xpt", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a024", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 24, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| PRENTPT | End Reference Time Point | Char | | Timing | Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference point referred to by PRENRTPT. Examples: \"2003-12-25\", \"VISIT 2\". | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": "pr.xpt", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0126_a025", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 126, "atom_index_on_page": 25, "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "¹In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a001", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 1, "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "PR – Assumptions", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 3, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a002", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 2, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. Some examples of procedures, by type, include the following:", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a003", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 3, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. Disease screening (e.g., mammogram, pap smear)", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a004", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 4, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. Endoscopic examinations (e.g., arthroscopy, diagnostic colonoscopy, therapeutic colonoscopy, diagnostic laparoscopy, therapeutic laparoscopy)", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a005", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 5, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. Diagnostic tests (e.g., amniocentesis, biopsy, catheterization, cutaneous oximetry, finger stick, fluorophotometry, imaging techniques (e.g., DXA scan, CT scan, MRI), phlebotomy, pulmonary function test, skin test, stress test, tympanometry)", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a006", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 6, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "d. Therapeutic procedures (e.g., ablation therapy, catheterization, cryotherapy, mechanical ventilation, phototherapy, radiation therapy/radiotherapy, thermotherapy)", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a007", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 7, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "e. Surgical procedures (e.g., curative surgery, diagnostic surgery, palliative surgery, therapeutic surgery, prophylactic surgery, resection, stenting, hysterectomy, tubal ligation, implantation)", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a008", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 8, "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The Procedures domain is based on the Interventions observation class. The extent of physiological effect may range from observable to microscopic. Regardless of the extent of effect or whether it is collected in the study, all collected procedures are represented in this domain. The protocol design should specify whether procedure information will be collected.Measurements obtained from procedures are to be represented in their respective Findings domain(s). For example, a biopsy may be performed to obtain a tissue sample that is then evaluated histopathologically. In this case, details of the biopsy procedure can be represented in the PR domain and the histopathology findings in the Microscopic Findings (MI) domain. Describing the relationship between PR and MI records (in RELREC) in this example is dependent on whether the relationship is collected, either explicitly or implicitly.", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": ["RELREC", "MI"], "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a009", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 9, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. In the Findings Observation Class, the test method is represented in the --METHOD variable (e.g., electrophoresis, gram stain, polymerase chain reaction). At times, the test method overlaps with diagnostic/therapeutic procedures (e.g., ultrasound, MRI, x-ray) in-scope for the PR domain. The following is recommended: If timing (start, end or duration) or an indicator populating PROCCUR, PRSTAT, or PRREASND is collected, then a PR record should be created. If only the findings from a procedure are collected, then --METHOD in the Findings domain(s) may be sufficient to reflect the procedure and a related PR record is optional. It is at the sponsor’s discretion whether to represent the procedure as both a test method (--METHOD) and related PR record.", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": ["PROCCUR", "PRSTAT", "PRREASND"], "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a010", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 10, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. PRINDC is used to represent a medical indication, a medical condition which makes a treatment advisable. The reason for a procedure may be something other than a medical indication. For example, an x-ray might be taken to determine whether a fracture was present. Reasons other than medical indications should be represented using the supplemental qualifier PRREAS (see Appendix C1, Supplemental Qualifiers Name Codes).", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": ["PRINDC", "PRREAS", "Appendix C1"], "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0127_a011", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 127, "atom_index_on_page": 11, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "4. Any identifier variables, timing variables, or interventions general observation-class qualifiers may be added to the PR domain, but the following qualifiers would generally not be used: --MOOD, --LOT.", "parent_section": "§6.1.5 [Procedures (PR)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
